Solving this system of equations, along with the unit vector constraint, will allow us to find the values of $a_1,$ $a_2,$ and $a_3,$ and hence the maximum value of the dot product.

\begin{align*}
\boxed{\text{The maximum value of } \mathbf{c} \cdot (\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{b}) \text{ is found by solving the system of equations above.}}
\end{align*}
